body:
After upgrading to Hardhat 2.11 I'm getting `Invalid Chai property: revertedWith` error when using `revertedWith` matcher in my tests (same thing happens when using the `reverted` matcher). Downgrading to 2.10 solves the issue.

Steps to reproduce:

* Create a new HH project (I've created a TS project)
* Install HH version 2.11 and hardhat-toolbox as usual
* Add a simple contract:

```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED
pragma solidity ^0.8.9;

contract Sample {
    function demo() external pure {
        revert("fail");
    }
}
```

* Add a test:

```ts
import { loadFixture } from "@nomicfoundation/hardhat-network-helpers";
import { expect } from "chai";
import { ethers } from "hardhat";
import type { Sample } from "../typechain-types";

describe("Sample", function() {
  async function dep() {
    const SampleFactory = await ethers.getContractFactory("Sample");
    const sample: Sample = await SampleFactory.deploy();
    await sample.deployed();

    return { sample }
  }

  it('reverts', async function() {
    const { sample } = await loadFixture(dep);

    await expect(sample.demo()).to.be.revertedWith('fail');
  })
});
```

* Run `npx hardhat test`
* You'll get an error:

```
1) Sample
       reverts:
     Error: Invalid Chai property: revertedWith
      at Object.proxyGetter [as get] (E:\sup\hh221_issue\node_modules\chai\lib\chai\utils\proxify.js:78:17)
      at Context.<anonymous> (E:\sup\hh221_issue\test\sample-test.ts:18:38)
      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)
```

* Locking HH to version 2.10.2 fixes this issue and the test works fine.

Here's a sample repo: https://github.com/bodrovis/HH211_issue

I'm using Node 16.
